            "body": "Hey, I'm attempting to take a stab at this and am running into some issues.\r\nUsing `nvim_open_win` to open a split is working fine but the main issue is with `nvim_win_set_config` and trying to turn a float into a split.\r\n\r\n@bfredl, you seem to be the one to talk to about this so pinging you.\r\n\r\nI initially tried to use `win_split`, but that just splits the current window, so I tried to use `win_split_ins` with the existing float `win_T` pointer, but that seems to cause an infinite loop. (And closing the window first causes a segfault). I guess I'm asking for some advice of how to properly get a split to open with the floating window handle that properly transfers the relevant window info. (And maybe some pointers about the stuff in `window.c`.)\r\n\r\nI can push my current work as a draft pr if you'd like more info!",
